entry.string:
6 months old baby presenting with history of hypotonia since birth and a recent history of 3 days fever and cough. Developed a truncular rash this morning. Exam shows severely hypotonic baby, no reflexes, muscle atrophy positive, no tongue fasciculations, normal gaze mouvements. He also has a flat head. no other dysmorphia. Chest with little diffuses ronchis, no wheezing. Maculopapular rash not blanching, not palpable, mostly on the trunk. no mucosal involvement.
URTI suspected but r/o pneumonie because of hypotonia viral rash hypotonia possibly due to perinatal hypoxemia: baby born at home at term but was "blue" for 5 minutes. 2 other babys well and healthy.
plan: chest x-ray. If normal,discharge and follow-up at the opd for complete evaluation.
took some medication from health center.no not remember the name of drug.

term baby,norn at home.difficult during birth,vaccination uo-to-date.here with fever for 3 days,fever no chill.wet cough since he was born ,no SOB,no cyanosis ,no dyspnae .yesterday there were some papule rash on the body.no pus or fluid inside the rashes ,no vomiting,breast feeding only,breast feeding well.passing urine and stool normal.
there are 3 children in the family.just him sick in the family.no TB contact no thalassemia history.
there are some small lymp node submandibular
